Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to survive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.02,0:00:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the attack of a roaring lion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.89,0:00:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, I did some \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.89,0:00:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—just quick—\Nchecking on various wildlife websites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.00,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and here’s what they say. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.00,0:00:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, they all give the same advice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.60,0:00:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,if you’re being attacked by a lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They say: “Hold your ground. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.47,0:00:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Never run or turn back.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.74,0:00:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, one website says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.61,0:00:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“A lion can run 50 miles per hour (80 km/h). \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.98,0:00:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“So stand still. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.12,0:00:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you run, you will only die tired.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.35,0:00:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.46,0:00:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,First Peter 5:9 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.73,0:00:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us exactly the same advice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.13,0:00:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Take your stand against him.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.40,0:00:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in this case \Nnot against a literal lion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.77,0:00:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but against that “roaring lion,” \NSatan the Devil, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.48,0:01:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,who is seeking to devour \Nevery single one of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.35,0:01:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ability to stand firm \Nwhen facing this lion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be able to oppose him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.09,0:01:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to refuse to be intimidated by him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.49,0:01:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to refuse to run away or turn back— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.49,0:01:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,requires what the apostle Peter \Nnext mentions there in verse 9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.13,0:01:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and Brother Crane \Nso nicely covered in his comment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.14,0:01:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to: “Take [our] stand against him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.74,0:01:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,firm in the faith.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.44,0:01:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To be successful, \Nwe must have complete trust \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.71,0:01:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and complete confidence in Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.42,0:01:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, in that regard, \Nlet’s look at an example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.89,0:01:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of someone in Bible times who had \Nthat kind of confidence in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.36,0:01:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in the days of King Jehoshaphat, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.89,0:01:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when Judah was threatened \Nby the combined forces \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.33,0:01:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,, of Moab, Ammon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.33,0:01:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the inhabitants \Nof the mountainous region of Seir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.37,0:02:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s begin by opening our Bibles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.10,0:02:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and reading 2 Chronicles 20:12. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.11,0:02:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So here Jehoshaphat is praying to Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.91,0:02:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s pouring out his heart to him, \Nand see what he says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.72,0:02:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“O our God, \Nwill you not execute judgment on them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“For we are powerless before this large crowd \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.23,0:02:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“that is coming against us; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.23,0:02:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“and we do not know what we should do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.53,0:02:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but our eyes are toward you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.54,0:02:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehoshaphat was facing the lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to Jehovah: \N‘We don’t know what to do.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.54,0:02:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehoshaphat had complete and total trust; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.55,0:02:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he had firm faith in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.38,0:02:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did Jehovah \Ntell Jehoshaphat to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.69,0:02:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See verse 17: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.39,0:02:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will not need to fight this battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.66,0:02:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your position.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.76,0:03:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that sound familiar? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.76,0:03:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take your position, stand still, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.57,0:03:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“and see the salvation of Jehovah \Nin your behalf. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.54,0:03:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“O Judah and Jerusalem, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.54,0:03:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“do not be afraid or be terrified. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.98,0:03:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Tomorrow go out against them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.41,0:03:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah will be with you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.45,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did Jehovah tell them to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: ‘Take a position \Nin opposition to that military force, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.09,0:03:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘stand firm, refuse to run away, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.69,0:03:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the salvation \Nthat will come from Jehovah.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.80,0:03:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in order to do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.80,0:03:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoshaphat and the people with him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.10,0:03:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,would need to have strong, firm, solid faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.48,0:03:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, to help the people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.48,0:03:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,look at what Jehoshaphat said to them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.58,0:03:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as they were getting ready for this battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.68,0:03:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 20, you see, \Njust about the middle of the verse, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.39,0:03:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: \N“Jehoshaphat stood up and said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.52,0:04:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Listen to me, O Judah \Nand you inhabitants of Jerusalem! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.99,0:04:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put faith in Jehovah your God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘so that you may be able to stand firm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put faith in his prophets, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.97,0:04:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will be successful.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s exactly what happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,See, with that kind of confidence in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with that firm trust in him, \Nwith that standing firm, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what did Jehovah do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.55,0:04:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, according to verses 22 and 23\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.32,0:04:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—you’ll remember what happened—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the men of Ammon, Moab, \Nand the inhabitants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.56,0:04:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the mountainous region of Seir, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.89,0:04:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they all went to striking down one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.20,0:04:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And verse 23 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.50,0:04:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the Ammonites and the Moabites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.77,0:04:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“turned against the inhabitants \Nof the mountainous region of Seir \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.51,0:04:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“to destroy and annihilate them; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.91,0:04:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“and when they finished \Nwith the inhabitants of Seir, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they helped to destroy one another.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.15,0:05:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah had rewarded \Ntheir firm faith in him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.15,0:05:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The weapons that had been formed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,against Jehoshaphat and his people \Nhad no success. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.19,0:05:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, \Nsometimes we think, of course, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.76,0:05:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that these kinds of situations \Nonly happened in Bible times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.53,0:05:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s amazing to see \Nhow our brothers in our modern day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,have had that same kind of faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.94,0:05:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and have stood firm against the lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.28,0:05:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are just a couple of experiences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.28,0:05:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that really touched my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.71,0:05:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s one about a brother \Nnamed Pavel from Russia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.75,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1958, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Pavel was arrested for religious activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Accompanying me to the train,” he says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.49,0:05:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“the officer [with me] said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.73,0:05:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Look at your wife for the last time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because you will never see her again.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.40,0:05:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there’s the lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“I spent six months \Nin solitary confinement before my trial. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“During interrogations, . . . \Nthe investigators did everything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.91,0:06:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“to undermine my faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.01,0:06:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sometimes violence was used. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.58,0:06:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I begged Jehovah \Nto give me the strength to stay firm.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.59,0:06:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But now look what happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.19,0:06:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“During a routine interrogation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“the investigator called me \Ninto his study and [he] said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.96,0:06:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Now we will show you \Nwhat your organization is doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.47,0:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then you can see \Nif it is God’s work or not!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Looking at me intently, he continued: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.11,0:06:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘This year your convention in New York \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘was attended by 253,000 people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.78,0:06:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘in two stadiums. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.78,0:06:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“The convention lasted eight days.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“The investigator strewed \Nthe table with photographs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“In one of them, \NI saw happy delegates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.03,0:06:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“in colorful native dress \Nembracing one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Another photo showed \NBrother Knorr giving a talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.50,0:06:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“and yet others showed the baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.53,0:07:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“The investigator could not even imagine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.74,0:07:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“what I was feeling at that moment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“I felt that I was attending the convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.61,0:07:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“without ever having left the prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“I felt new strength flooding into me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.18,0:07:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“[It was just what] I had needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.25,0:07:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . And Jehovah generously \Nblessed me in a special way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.46,0:07:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ready to endure further.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that amazing?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s another similar experience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.43,0:07:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,1960, also in Russia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.17,0:07:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a large publicized trial \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,About 300 persons \Nwere present in the courtroom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.84,0:07:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,including many of our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.01,0:07:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as the evidence—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.01,0:07:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As evidence against the brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.15,0:07:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the prosecutor decided to present \Na letter from Nathan H. Knorr. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.15,0:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the brothers \Nwho attended the trial said this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“The prosecutor loudly began to read a letter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.06,0:07:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“that had been intercepted by the KGB \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“from Brother Knorr \Nto the brothers in the Soviet Union. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.07,0:08:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“For all of us Witnesses present in the hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“it was a wonderful gift from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“This letter warmed our hearts! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“We heard wise counsel from the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.08,0:08:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and encouragement to serve \Nour fellow believers lovingly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to stay faithful [even] under trials. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“The prosecutor read the letter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.15,0:08:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the beginning to the very end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.06,0:08:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“We listened with rapt attention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.72,0:08:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed to us that we were \Nattending a convention!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, brothers, what additional lessons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.17,0:08:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,do we learn from these two experiences? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.77,0:08:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When we stand our ground against Satan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.57,0:08:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,firm in the faith, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then Jehovah will do just what he promised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.48,0:08:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Peter 5:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.38,0:08:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see what it says there? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.52,0:08:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“But after you have suffered a little while, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:09:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“the God of all undeserved kindness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“who called you to his everlasting glory \Nin union with Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.49,0:09:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“will himself finish your training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will make you firm, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.80,0:09:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“he will make you strong, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.90,0:09:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,he will firmly ground you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.84,0:09:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.84,0:09:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,can we survive the attack of a roaring lion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.11,0:09:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.11,0:09:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,With firm faith, let’s stand fast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.18,0:09:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the salvation from Jehovah. \N
